caption: Favorite place by far. Flavors and variety are on point, they offer zucchini noodles for base, and they offer free mochi or mise soup with a check-in with another ratings app that starts with Y and ends with p. Super fast and friendly service is also a constant across all their locations.

A really chill place to go, the red curry was  very good, and my wife enjoyed her meal as well. The tea and water did taste a little like dish detergent. Maybe they'd just finished rush washing the cups?
Good food, horrible service. Order take-out.

I live next door and always get the noodle soup. These guys are legit. Good food, decent price, no frills atmosphere, pretty much what you want when you want good Thai food without the “extra” nonsense.
Delicious Thai food. Fresh and spicy.
I honestly enjoy the food and service, excellent area close to my residence. The employees are always very nice. I highly recommend this place.
Safety precautions in place. Tasty! Friendly staff.
Great food and ambiance.

Excellent place to go for some thai food and a drink. The main chef is from Thailand and does a great job. Drunken noodles and stir friend basil were outstanding. Beer is cold and fresh. When the weather is nice, great place to sit outside. Prices are... look, its an expensive area to rent restaurant space, so dont expect bargain basement prices. But if you're in the area you're not really gonna find cheaper eats.

Their traditional noodle dishes aren’t bad. However, the Crispy Basil Duck is horrible. I’ve had many different versions of it and this was by far the worst. The best versions are sliced or pulled so that there is an even proportion of fat to meat, and pan fried with aromatics.  Their version was a mess of uneven chunks that were cheaply breaded and deep fried into a disgusting clump. The sauce they served on the side was a lazy goo of sugar, basil, and red bell peppers. Whoever made this either winged it or didn’t care to look up the recipe online. We ended up throwing it away. I’ll not be reordering from them.
Goid food,  very good service.
The food was very tasty, only thing the service was really slow
This place is incredible !! The food was awesome !
Food was very good but portions were small.
Amazing food and excellent service! I will definitely come back!!
New favorite place right by my job. Spicy spicy spicy. Ask for less spice.

Told the guy my dish was sooo spicy I couldn’t it/it hurt my stomach - he told me that’s how the dish is to be mad and was upset because I had eaten a 1/3 of it (because I was trying not to go back to Charm Thai /got takeout). Would not recommend this place to anyone but only as a LAST RESORT. Also super expensive, with small serving sizes.
Solid meal, nothing spectacular, but not bad.
Looks like it was permanently closed wasn’t  it? Drove pass so many time doesn’t seems like they’re open :/

Everything was delicious!! Salmon well cooked, not spicy, salad and rolls also great! I also eat a Wonton soup with a very delicate and delicious flavor.  I'd like to go back and try a different dish! The only thing is the place inside is very dark and was hard for me to see what I was eating!
The best Thai resturant ever.
Great Thai food. Good one.

Amazing Thai food in foggy Bottom. Fast and friendly service with a smile. I tried it twice once for carry out and once for dine in. I was amazed how the lady asked me water even when I wanted carry out. Good service overall.
Dinner and ice cold beer. Awesome place.

The food is horrible everything is extremely greasy oily and way to salty stay away from this restaurant it will cause a heart attack I give them a negative 50 for a rating!!!!!!!

Delicious. Clean. Fast Cook in front of you. Cheap place.

Ok for Thai food, but will definitely try some others. Crab cakes were rubbery bit that may be the Thai version of them. I ordered the pad Thai spicy and it was not spicy at all. Friendly servers and it all came out fast and hot, though.
A lovely family owned Thai restaurant. Very friendly and warm. The food was great and service was simply wonderful. Thank you!

Waited 20 minutes for an appetizer (spring rolls) despite being only three total people in the restaurant. When the appetizer came, they were literally the egg rolls from the freezer section at the grocery store. Waited another 40 minutes for food and watched the waiter leave. When I asked the lady if we could just pay for our drinks and appetizers, she literally yelled at me saying that our food was coming. Literally yelled! Food was then brought out immediately.
The food was good and reasonbly priced
Difficult. It was not really good, but not really bad. Staff friendly, ambiente ok, average. We all were hungry and did not explore Georgetown, which was a mistake. Lots of cozy looking restaurants.

I went there for an event with my organization a few weeks ago. We had a buffet set up and people dancing on the second floor. I went to the bar and asked for water. I was asked by the bartender if I was ordering food and I responded no. He then asked me again and I responded that I was with the group having the event. He gave me a glass of water and I returned to my friends.  A few minutes later, he approaches my friends and asks them if I am with them. They reply yes and he asks them again. Other people at the event respond that I am with the group. I'm not sure why the bartender singled me out among the entire party, but the encounter left me feeling uncomfortable as the only person of color in my party.  The food was okay, but I would recommend that the restaurant work on their personnel and provide more interpersonal communication/diversity training. I've never experienced such behavior from restaurant staff in the entire DC area.
Great service and good Thai food.

Food was incredible, the service was stellar and the music made me fall in love with the place. I highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a quality meal with a reasonable price and a beer to wash it all down.
Conveniently located Thai restaurant with excellent Pad Thai and Thai Basil.
Under new ownership. Great staff and fantastic food. Eat here!!

Order a couple of dishes to share. Pad Thai with beef and shrimp pad see ew. Well the picture will show you that they gave us beef for both dishes. The pad Thai was one of the worst dishes I have ever had. Lacked flavor, and I’ve had more enjoyment from a cup of noodles. I’d avoid this at all costs. Even though they got the dish wrong, the pad see ew was actually decent. Overall, I’d avoid this place if you’ve ever had Thai food before.

Best Pad Thai and Drunken Noodle in DMV area, Hands Down!
The food was delicious. The vibe was relaxed. Well priced. Although we preferred wine, their Thai beer did not disappoint. The drunken noodles was mouthwatering.  Can't wait to go back.
Delicious food, friendly service
Pretty disappointing for the price.
Not a bad place. Food is clean and portion sizes very decent.  Definitely Thai food but not the best. May need to ask for it a bit spicier. Prices a good!

Relatively budget friendly place. The pad Thai tasted very good. Seafood tasted fresh. Ambience is pretty run of the mill. Service is good. The place is good for families.

This is a decent Thai restaurant. There's nothing much to say about the location or the dwelling itself but the food was decent.

Reasonably priced for portion size. Lunch visit, no wait. Given 2 different menus, a set lunch with options and the regular menu. Chose to go with the regular, however, server had to come back 2x to tell me my first 2 appetizer choices (chicken satay and Thai crab cakes ) were not available. Finally settled on the fried Wantons, and entrees was Siam Fried Rice and Penang Curry Chicken. To-go was Chicken Pad Thai which was a bit sweet for my taste. Server was excellent, very courteous, friendly yet in a very professional demeanor.
Service was amazing, and the food was even better. I will definitely be back!
I ordered the Drunken noodles mild (spicy are for the brave) and it’s was prefect! Had the right bit of spicy, good amount of noodles and beef, def going back.

Liked it so much, we came back 3 years later. We stopped for lunch 3 years ago while touring GW Univ. This week, we were in town for a funeral and decided we'd go into the city for dinner specifically because we liked it so much. It didn't let us down. Granted, it was early in the evening, 5ish, but we sat right down, ordered and our food was out in minutes. Wife and kid always get the Pad See Ew and they loved it. I'm the kind that chooses something different, this time I got the Pineapple Fried Rice with pork and it was delicious. So much food, couldn't fit in dessert. Helped a lot for our walk around the mall afterwards. We'll always go back if we ever get back into town.
Good food!
Best pad thai noodles you can get! Local place - simple. The rest of the menu isn't great but they do pad thai really well, and that's what we have when we go.
Great happy hour drink deals. Love the fried rice.

Ordered through Uber Eats. The food was tasty until I got to my mango sticky rice. The mango was rotten and I had to throw it out. Annoyed I wasted $7 on rotten food. Makes me wonder about the cleanliness of their restaurant if they didn't notice rotten fruit as they arranged it.
Home style cooking - large portions
Reasonable food.

Pretty average price for lunch (~$10 for 1 entree), but wow the drunken noodle and red curry were both incredibly delicious. Will definitely come here again. Yes, drunken noodle is greasy. Cozy place with friendly staff (fast service), and it's the perfect place to grab a quick bite for lunch with a friend.

food overpriced.  I got rice noodles with beef, it was grease, and the portion was small. I still like them. Much better than other Thai places in this town

Worst attempt at Thai cuisine I have ever had the misfortune to experience.  I had ordered delivered take-out, so the food was on my table after delivery. I thought I had received the wrong order, as the "duck" was not recognizable, and the pork with garlic and black pepper contained neither.  I called the restaurant and spokes with the chef. I am American but I also speak Thai. He told me I had received the correct order. Since I had already eaten half the food, I asked for a credit of,half the price, to which he agreed.  I would avoid this restaurant if you wish to eat Thai food which looks and tastes like Thai food.

Food was good except my husband had two small insects floating in his Long Island iced tea... Waitress took the drink away without looking at it and didn't offer any apology. A man came out, apologized and stated they were in the gin bottle, and that they threw the bottle out.... In the gin bottle... Really? Will never return.  Edit: posted image of insects to their photos
Fast, friendly service and delicious food. The Panang Pork and Thai Iced Tea were excellent!
Wonderful service! Prompt greetings! Order to share The Sampler, followed by Seafood Salad and the favorite of all: Drunken Noodles!! Iced Coffee is just right too! Waitress was nice and friendly!

They have some really good not expensive dishes like Pad Woon Sen for example or their different fried rices are great. But some dishes are too small though (bento boxes are too small for example) It's very nice inside, always fresh flowers...
Got the 3 course dinner for two. Everything tasted great. Drunken noodles are a little spicy but delicious. My wife loved the panang curry.
Really great Thai food! I always get the Pad See Ew.
Massaman curry was delicious. Ordered online for pickup, and they had it ready very quickly.

Quiet little Thai restaurant near GWU campus in Georgetown with solid noodle dishes and curries. The drunken noodles have a good kick to them (baseline of three chili peppers —ask for four if you're daring!) and the red duck curry has a nice flavor. The evening atmosphere is nice and quiet, making it an excellent date spot, though it can get crowded on Fridays and Saturdays. Good place for dinner if you're in the area!

went here by accident with my family for dinner on a wednesday.  the red curry with pork was excellent, the Tum Yum shrimp soup was very flavorful and excellent, the Thai dumplings were also excellent.  the cashew pork and chicken wasn't quite as good, but still good.  we had a Guiness and a Heinkens, both were fine, and the water was fine.  the service was very nice, quick, very friendly.  I would definitely go back.
Very fast service, and the Pad Thai was fantastic. Highly recommended!
